    "slides": [
        {
            "id": "s_l3_1",
            "type": "text",
            "title": "What if not? 🤷",
            "content": "Sometimes you want to do something if the condition is `true`, and something ELSE if it's `false`.\n\nUse the `else` keyword."
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l3_2",
            "type": "quiz",
            "title": "Quick Check 🧠",
            "content": "",
            "quizData": {
                "id": "q_l3_1",
                "type": "multiple_choice",
                "question": "When does the 'else' block run?",
                "options": [
                    {
                        "id": "opt1",
                        "text": "If the 'if' condition is true",
                        "isCorrect": false
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "opt2",
                        "text": "If the 'if' condition is false",
                        "isCorrect": true
                    }
                ],
                "explanation": "`else` covers everything not caught by the `if`."
            }
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l3_3",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "Example 🌞🌚",
            "content": "One path or the other.",
            "codeSnippet": "let isDay = false;\n\nif (isDay) {\n  console.log('Sun is out');\n} else {\n  console.log('Moon is out');\n}",
            "codeLanguage": "javascript",
            "canRunCode": true
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l3_4",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "Even More Options 🔀",
            "content": "You can check multiple conditions using `else if`.",
            "codeSnippet": "let color = 'red';\n\nif (color === 'red') {\n  console.log('Stop!');\n} else if (color === 'green') {\n  console.log('Go!');\n} else {\n  console.log('Wait.');\n}",
            "codeLanguage": "javascript",
            "canRunCode": true
        },
